Fetch the Bolt Cutters is a strange and exceptional record, even within the context of an uncommon career.
Apple is especially keen to hijack the rhythms of work songs and playground chants.
There is a lot of looking back on Fetch the Bolt Cutters.
The younger Apple’s output was always preternaturally wise, but Fetch the Bolt Cutters seeks to unlearn the studio gloss of her previous albums while making full use of all her experiences.
It previously said that Fetch the Bolt Cutters was Apple’s fourth album: it is her fifth.